column5: Riding off the jitters

This time I was mentally prepared for the vukojebina and also chose an easy trail, so this whole endeavor was much less dramatic (and traumatic) than last year. But being tired and sleep-deprived still made it mildly painful 😁

Loose loose rocks that make every step a gamble, tearing through groves of thorny whatever drawing blood from my arms and legs -- now we're talking! Also, my Alex shoes are getting pretty worn out 😢 As am I 😂
